title = 'About Software Commons'
[---]
Software Commons is [a multi-stakeholder cooperative][1] of software producers
and consumers, both corporate and individual. Our purpose is **to sustain a
healthy commons of publicly shared software**. We [balance user freedom and
developer sustainability][2], in order to protect against both [enclosure][3]
and the [tragedy of the commons][4]. We utilize two mechanisms: [licensing][5],
and [Fair Share][6]. We recognize both [Open Source Projects][7] and [Open
Products][8] as legitimate, and we celebrate software sharing and
sustainability wherever we see it, whether from members of Software Commons or
not.

