## Comparison with the Open Source Initiative

The [Open Source Initiative][14] was founded in 1998 to popularize [Free
Software][15]. The Free and Open Source Software (FOSS) movement is built on
user freedom as an overarching moral imperative.

<img src="./four-freedoms.webp">

From a commons standpoint, therefore, while FOSS protects against enclosure, it
does not protect against harmful free-riding and the tragedy of the commons.
Software Commons includes [Open Source Projects][16], and through [Fair
Share][17] we protect FOSS against the tragedy of the commons, while continuing
to protect against enclosure through [licensing][18].

